171
00:10:02.424 --> 00:10:06.144
This is where, for example, our discussions about risk are important.

172
00:10:06.184 --> 00:10:09.313
Is it high risk or average risk? Does average risk have a meaning?

173
00:10:10.243 --> 00:10:12.004
You have to be able to define a study design.

174
00:10:12.064 --> 00:10:14.984
Is it a case control versus an interventional study, for example?

175
00:10:15.064 --> 00:10:16.384
Those are very different things.

176
00:10:17.924 --> 00:10:21.544
Tina just mentioned the target condition of the test is something that is

177
00:10:22.204 --> 00:10:25.264
